<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: bus_element_link
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link">
A <b>bus_element_link</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> and a  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> that implements the ARM concept of <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:arm:Network_functional_design_view_arm.Bus_element_link"/>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR1">
The related element shall not be the relating element. 
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR2">
The <b>bus_element_link</b> shall relate to only a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition"/> or a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition"/> in the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR3">
The <b>bus_element_link</b> shall relate to only a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition"/> or a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition"/> in the <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.relating_product_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR4">
The types of <b>bus_element_link</b> shall be only <b>bus_element_link</b>,  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/>, and  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR5
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR5">
The name attribute of the  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> supertype shall be an empty string.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR6
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR6">
The name attribute of the  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> supertype shall be an empty string.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_element_link.WR7
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.wr:WR7">
Each <b>bus_element_link</b> shall be referenced at least once by a  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
UR: bus_element_link.UR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link.ur:UR1">
The combination of related, relating attributes inherited from  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> be unique within a population of <b>bus_element_link</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: bus_structural_definition
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition">
<p>
A <b>bus_structural_definition</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> that implements the ARM
concept of  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:arm:Network_functional_design_view_arm.Bus_structural_definition"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_structural_definition.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition.wr:WR1">
The <b>bus_structural_definition</b> shall relate to at least one  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_element_link"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_structural_definition.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition.wr:WR2">
The <b>bus_structural_definition</b> shall have at most one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/>
that relates to another  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> to specify the 'functional unit
network terminal definition bus assignment'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: bus_structural_definition.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition.wr:WR3">
The <b>bus_structural_definition</b> shall be a connected structure and shall not have any vertex with a degree greater than 2.  The number of vertices shall equal the number of links + 1.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: component_functional_terminal
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_terminal">
<p>
A <b>component_functional_terminal</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that implements the ARM
concept of  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:arm:Network_functional_design_view_arm.Functional_unit_terminal"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_terminal.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_terminal.wr:WR1">
The <b>component_functional_terminal</b> shall be an aspect of the shape of a
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_unit"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_terminal.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_terminal.wr:WR2">
The <b>component_functional_terminal</b> shall be related to exactly one
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_usage_view:mim:Network_functional_usage_view_mim.functional_unit_terminal_definition"/> as the 'instantiated terminal'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_terminal.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_terminal.wr:WR3">
The <b>component_functional_terminal</b> shall be related to at most one
property of a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition"/> as the 
'functional unit terminal bus assignment'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_terminal.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_terminal.wr:WR4">
The <b>component_functional_terminal</b> shall be related to at most one 
property of a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition"/> as the
'functional unit terminal node assignment'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: component_functional_unit
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_unit">
<p>
A <b>component_functional_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> that implements the ARM
concept of  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:arm:Network_functional_design_view_arm.Functional_unit"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_unit.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_unit.wr:WR1">
The <b>component_functional_unit</b> shall have the context element named
'functional occurrence'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_unit.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_unit.wr:WR2">
The <b>component_functional_unit</b> shall have at least one
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_terminal"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_unit.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_unit.wr:WR3">
The <b>component_functional_unit</b> shall be related to exactly one
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_usage_view:mim:Network_functional_usage_view_mim.functional_unit"/> as the 'instantiated functional unit'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: component_functional_unit.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.component_functional_unit.wr:WR4">
The <b>component_functional_unit</b> shall be related to exactly one
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_usage_view:mim:Network_functional_usage_view_mim.functional_unit"/> that has a context element with a name of 'functional network
design' as the 'network composition'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: network_node_definition
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition">
<p>
A <b>network_node_definition</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> that implements the ARM
concept of  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:arm:Network_functional_design_view_arm.Functional_unit_network_node_definition"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: network_node_definition.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition.wr:WR1">
The <b>network_node_definition</b> shall have its context element with a name
of 'functional network design'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: network_node_definition.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition.wr:WR2">
The <b>network_node_definition</b> shall have at most one property that relates
to at most one   <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.product_definition_shape"/> of a 
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_usage_view:mim:Network_functional_usage_view_mim.functional_unit_terminal_definition"/> to specify the 
'functional unit network terminal definition node assignment'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: network_node_definition.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.network_node_definition.wr:WR3">
The <b>network_node_definition</b> shall be related to exactly one
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_usage_view:mim:Network_functional_usage_view_mim.functional_unit"/> that has a context element with a name of 'functional network
design' as the 'functional unit network node'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint</b> rule
constrains the related and relating  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> for a
 <express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship"/> when it is used as a functional unit network
terminal definition bus assignment.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint.wr:WR1">
IF  <express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship"/>.name = 'functional unit network terminal 
definition bus assignment' THEN SELF.<express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship.relating_property_definition"/>.definition 
shall be a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.functional_unit_network_terminal_definition_bus_assignment_constraint.wr:WR2">
IF  <express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship"/>.name = 'functional unit network terminal 
definition bus assignment' THEN SELF.<express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship.related_property_definition"/> shall be a 
 <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.product_definition_shape"/> that is the <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect.of_shape"/> of a 
 <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_usage_view:mim:Network_functional_usage_view_mim.functional_unit_terminal_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: functional_unit_terminal_bus_assignment_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.functional_unit_terminal_bus_assignment_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>functional_unit_terminal_bus_assignment_constraint</b> rule constrains the
related and relating  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> of a  <express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship"/>
when it is a functional unit terminal bus assignment.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: functional_unit_terminal_bus_assignment_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Network_functional_design_view_mim.functional_unit_terminal_bus_assignment_constraint.wr:WR1">
IF  <express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship"/> name = 'functional unit terminal 
bus assignment' THEN the <express_ref linkend="material_property_definition_schema:ir_express:material_property_definition_schema.property_definition_relationship.relating_property_definition"/> definition shall be
a  <express_ref linkend="Network_functional_design_view:mim:Network_functional_design_view_mim.bus_structural_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
